(91, 1, '2016-03-28 11:10:52', '2016-03-28 11:10:52', '<img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-90" src="your_website_url_here/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Depositphotos_20437641_original-1024x680.jpg" alt="Depositphotos_20437641_original" width="710" height="471" />\r\n\r\nTraveling passion always ruled my life. But in 2012 everything just went into overdrive. What I thought would be just a 2 month trip to Norway unexpectedly turned into a 2 years long journey. And believe me, I did not plan it that way, though enjoyed immensely. Meeting my college friends in Oslo, I ended up journeying all the way from Scandinavia to South Africa. Then I slowly made my way from Portugal to Brazil and down to Chile. I simply couldn’t stop. Luckily, I had some savings from the times I''ve been employed. :-) In short, to me traveling is not a simple holiday or a relaxation session. Laying in the sun on the beach... For me, it''s all about venturing out into the unknown. Also, during a trip one can easily travel beyond their comfort zone. So trying new dishes, enjoying other cultures, doing silly things... It''s all a part of the process! I personally perceive each new city, country or a natural landscape with an awe of a newborn child! On my blog, I hope to encourage others to travel more. By sharing my unique traveling vantage points and tips, I want to enhance the journey for all my readers! Be sure to use my destination guides, city reviews and countries travel itineraries. After a prolonged period of globetrotting, my new aim is to stick to the ground for a while. Still, it does not hurt to travel across the USA from time to time. Being a New Yorker definitely added to my open mind and love for new cultures. So when I am not doing scuba diving for sea shells in Aruba or eating guinea pig in Ecuador, you can probably find me living somewhere along the East Coast. I sincerely try to propagate an independent traveling. By that, I do not mean solo traveling. Rather I mean making up your own plans instead of going on an organized tour. Traveling this way can be more challenging, but ultimately, impression-wise it''s much more rewarding. Good luck on your travels, and thanks for stopping by!\r\n\r\n—   Steve Davis', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-28 11:10:52', '2016-03-28 11:10:52', '', 18, 'your_website_url_here/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
