(153, 1, '2016-03-31 14:20:37', '2016-03-31 14:20:37', '<h1>Traveling as a Lifestyle</h1>\r\n<img class="size-large wp-image-127 alignleft" src="your_website_url_here/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Depositphotos_48037363_original-791x1024.jpg" alt="Depositphotos_48037363_original" width="710" height="919" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTraveling passion always ruled my life. But in 2012 everything just went into overdrive.\r\n\r\nWhat I thought would be just a 2 month trip to Norway unexpectedly turned into a 2 years long journey. And believe me, I did not plan it that way, though enjoyed immensely. Meeting my college friends in Oslo, I ended up journeying all the way from Scandinavia to South Africa. Then I slowly made my way from Portugal to Brazil and down to Chile. I simply couldn’t stop. Luckily, I had some savings from the times I''ve been employed. :-)\r\n\r\nIn short, to me traveling is not a simple holiday or a relaxation session. Laying in the sun on the beach... For me, it''s all about venturing out into the unknown. Also, during a trip one can easily travel beyond their comfort zone.\r\n\r\nSo trying new dishes, enjoying other cultures, doing silly things... It''s all a part of the process!\r\n\r\nI personally perceive each new city, country or a natural landscape with an awe of a newborn child!\r\n\r\nOn my blog, I hope to encourage others to travel more. By sharing my unique traveling vantage points and tips, I want to enhance the journey for all my readers!\r\n\r\nBe sure to use my destination guides, city reviews and countries travel itineraries.\r\n\r\nAfter a prolonged period of globetrotting, my new aim is to stick to the ground for a while.\r\n\r\nStill, it does not hurt to travel across the USA from time to time.\r\n\r\nBeing a New Yorker definitely added to my open mind and love for new cultures. So when I am not doing scuba diving for sea shells in Aruba or eating guinea pig in Ecuador, you can probably find me living somewhere along the East Coast.\r\n\r\nI sincerely try to propagate an independent traveling. By that, I do not mean solo traveling. Rather I mean making up your own plans instead of going on an organized tour. Traveling this way can be more challenging, but ultimately, impression-wise it''s much more rewarding.\r\n\r\nGood luck on your travels, and thanks for stopping by!\r\n\r\n<strong>—   Steve Davis</strong>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-31 14:20:37', '2016-03-31 14:20:37', '', 18, 'your_website_url_here/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
